rComments: Good professor! Explain everything clearly. Exam is easy, too. If you need one elective course out of telfer faculty, chose this!

Really good lectures. He can explain a complex topic in a really easy manner for you to understand it. He is highly accessible in office hours and always answers emails in a cordial manner. If you need an extension, he will give it to you. He bases his lectures in the textbook, but the most important things for exams will be in his slides.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Professor Manjunath's lectures were easy and simple to follow. His discussion groups were really helpful, maybe as even effective as in-class. If you do the problem sets and study off them for the midterm and final exam, it is easy to achieve a great mark. His problem sets are very flexible. I would definitely take his classes again.

Professor Manjunath is extremely clear about his expectations. Lectures are posted and he is very accessible outside of class. His lectures are very straightforward and he is willing to answer questions in different ways to make sure that his students are grasping the content. His grading is very fair and his assignments reflect the midterms well

Manjunath is one of the best lecturers I have had. He's super nice and took time to explain things people did not understand. He is very easy going and wants people to do well. His lectures are necessary to pass due to the difficulty of the material. As far as I can tell everyone who attended all the lectures passed the final when I took the class.

He is probably the most straightforward professor I've ever had. He said he doesn't like cumulative exams and marking so his marking scheme is literally problem sets and 3 multiple choice midterms of equal weight. His teaching is a bit too fast but he tries to maintain pace and makes sure that people can keep up with the lectures. Great prof.

Vikram was a great prof and his expectations are very straight forward. Both midterms and the final only consisted of 40 multiple choice. His problem sets that he assigns on the LMS do a good job in preparing you for the examinations. He does a really good job explaining whatever concept you need help with during his office hours. Don't skip class.
